This project was part of the course "New Product Development & Branding" at Marshall School of Business (USC).

It involved the analysis of two surveys taken by 190 respondents in total, as well as two focus groups. The project revolved around Target's Brand Equity through the analysis of the brand (4P's, competitor analysis, perceptual map, 3/4 factor model, etc.) and development & testing of ideas for new products and category lines.
